cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on the ability of LSTMs to capture syntactic structure. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning and neural networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves training and testing the LSTM architecture, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses language models, which can be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as language models are often used in image captioning tasks.
